26struct TextureCaps
27{
28 TextureCaps();
29 TextureCaps(const TextureCaps &other);
30 ~TextureCaps();
31
32 // Supports for basic texturing: glTexImage, glTexSubImage, etc
33 bool texturable = false;
34
35 // Support for linear or anisotropic filtering
36 bool filterable = false;
37
38 // Support for being used as a framebuffer attachment, i.e. glFramebufferTexture2D
39 bool textureAttachment = false;
40
41 // Support for being used as a renderbuffer format, i.e. glFramebufferRenderbuffer
42 bool renderbuffer = false;
43
44 // Support for blend modes while being used as a framebuffer attachment
45 bool blendable = false;
46
47 // Set of supported sample counts, only guaranteed to be valid in ES3.
48 SupportedSampleSet sampleCounts;
49
50 // Get the maximum number of samples supported
51 GLuint getMaxSamples() const;
52
53 // Get the number of supported samples that is at least as many as requested. Returns 0 if
54 // there are no sample counts available
55 GLuint getNearestSamples(GLuint requestedSamples) const;
56};

62class TextureCapsMap final : angle::NonCopyable
63{
64 public:
65 TextureCapsMap();
66 ~TextureCapsMap();
67
68 // These methods are deprecated. Please use angle::Format for new features.
69 void insert(GLenum internalFormat, const TextureCaps &caps);
70 const TextureCaps &get(GLenum internalFormat) const;
71
72 void clear();
73
74 // Prefer using angle::Format methods.
75 const TextureCaps &get(angle::FormatID formatID) const;
76 void set(angle::FormatID formatID, const TextureCaps &caps);
77
78 private:
79 TextureCaps &get(angle::FormatID formatID);
80
81 // Indexed by angle::FormatID
82 std::array<TextureCaps, angle::kNumANGLEFormats> mFormatData;
83};

115 // NOTE: GL_KHR_texture_compression_astc_hdr must be enabled separately. Support for the

683// Pointer to a boolean memeber of the Extensions struct
684using ExtensionBool = bool Extensions::*;
685
686struct ExtensionInfo
687{
688 // If this extension can be enabled or disabled with glRequestExtension
689 // (GL_ANGLE_request_extension)
690 bool Requestable = false;
691 bool Disablable = false;
692
693 // Pointer to a boolean member of the Extensions struct
694 ExtensionBool ExtensionsMember = nullptr;
695};
696
697using ExtensionInfoMap = std::map<std::string, ExtensionInfo>;
698const ExtensionInfoMap &GetExtensionInfoMap();
699
700struct Limitations
701{
702 Limitations();
703 Limitations(const Limitations &other);
704
705 Limitations &operator=(const Limitations &other);
706
707 // Renderer doesn't support gl_FrontFacing in fragment shaders
708 bool noFrontFacingSupport = false;
709
710 // Renderer doesn't support GL_SAMPLE_ALPHA_TO_COVERAGE
711 bool noSampleAlphaToCoverageSupport = false;
712
713 // In glVertexAttribDivisorANGLE, attribute zero must have a zero divisor
714 bool attributeZeroRequiresZeroDivisorInEXT = false;
715
716 // Unable to support different values for front and back faces for stencil refs and masks
717 bool noSeparateStencilRefsAndMasks = false;
718
719 // Renderer doesn't support non-constant indexing loops in fragment shader
720 bool shadersRequireIndexedLoopValidation = false;
721
722 // Renderer doesn't support Simultaneous use of GL_CONSTANT_ALPHA/GL_ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_ALPHA
723 // and GL_CONSTANT_COLOR/GL_ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_COLOR blend functions.
724 bool noSimultaneousConstantColorAndAlphaBlendFunc = false;
725
726 // D3D9 does not support flexible varying register packing.
727 bool noFlexibleVaryingPacking = false;
728
729 // D3D does not support having multiple transform feedback outputs go to the same buffer.
730 bool noDoubleBoundTransformFeedbackBuffers = false;
731
732 // D3D does not support vertex attribute aliasing
733 bool noVertexAttributeAliasing = false;
734
735 // Renderer doesn't support GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE=GL_NONE on a shadow sampler.
